cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with compression and quantization of vectors, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of wrapped spherical codes and the Leech lattice suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and geometry (cs.DS), while the evaluation of the performance of compression schemes involves numerical methods and simulations (cs.MM). Finally, the mention of error exponents and practical implementation hints at a control systems perspective (cs.SY).
